WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:03.210
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:03.210 --> 00:04.080
Ash, what are you
doing here?

00:04.080 --> 00:05.040
Just tying up
odds and ends.

00:05.040 --> 00:07.000
You got to love
odds and ends.

00:07.000 --> 00:08.540
Shut it down.
What?

00:08.540 --> 00:11.120
John specifically said
"Do not have sex with her."

00:11.120 --> 00:14.170
I-If I do nothing --
no treatments --

00:14.170 --> 00:15.120
how long do I have?

00:15.120 --> 00:16.420
You won't live
beyond a year.

00:16.420 --> 00:17.670
Winner takes all.

00:17.670 --> 00:19.670
If I beat you,
you're gonna fight cancer.

00:19.670 --> 00:22.380
If I win, I am not getting
any treatment,

00:22.380 --> 00:25.670
and you can't mention it
ever again to me or anyone.

00:25.670 --> 00:26.540
Game on.

00:28.170 --> 00:29.330
I win!

00:29.330 --> 00:32.540
Dare me to do anything,
and make it really hard.

00:32.540 --> 00:34.420
I dare you to get chemo.

00:34.420 --> 00:36.580
Game's over.
I can't believe you said that.

00:36.580 --> 00:38.580
Mathers:
That's your baby.
[ Chuckles ]

00:38.580 --> 00:40.040
Pretending you're
not the father --

00:40.040 --> 00:41.500
I know it's unbearable.

00:41.500 --> 00:44.000
It's got to be the hardest thing
I've ever done in my life.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.710
I just want
what's best for you.

00:47.000 --> 00:48.750
Gary:
Seems like a good dude.

00:48.750 --> 00:50.500
We're working on a case
together.

00:50.500 --> 00:52.330
Well, I hope you win.

00:52.330 --> 00:54.170
You deserve to be happy,
Katherine.

00:55.920 --> 00:58.920
[ The Cure's "Lovesong" plays ]

00:58.920 --> 01:05.040
♪♪

01:05.040 --> 01:14.170
♪♪

01:14.170 --> 01:16.170
It's so beautiful
up here.

01:17.750 --> 01:20.250
I can almost forget
that I'm dangling

01:20.250 --> 01:23.710
12,000 feet above the ground
in a tiny metal tube.

01:23.710 --> 01:25.000
[ Chuckles ]

01:25.000 --> 01:26.580
You worry too much.

01:26.580 --> 01:28.170
Mm.

01:28.170 --> 01:29.380
I love it.

01:29.380 --> 01:33.750
I get to leave all my problems
on the ground below.

01:33.750 --> 01:36.250
[ Rumbling ]
[ Groans ]
Oh! What was that?

01:36.250 --> 01:37.960
Just choppy air.

01:37.960 --> 01:39.250
Don't worry.

01:40.710 --> 01:42.040
[ Engine revving,
alarm blaring ]

01:42.040 --> 01:43.790
[ Groans ]

01:43.790 --> 01:45.880
What can I do?

01:45.880 --> 01:48.170
Chad, I can't help you
if you won't let me.

01:48.170 --> 01:49.960
Relax, I got this.

01:49.960 --> 01:53.000
I don't have time for this,
I have to get to the movies.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.330
Then go.
Who's stopping you, Mags?

01:55.330 --> 01:57.670
How can I leave if you can't
even tell which way is up?

01:57.670 --> 02:01.000
Mags, Mags, it's fine.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.830
♪♪

02:03.830 --> 02:05.830
[ Rumbling, alarm blaring ]
Oh! We're going down.

02:05.830 --> 02:07.170
Pull it up!
Electronic voice:
Pull up! Pull up!

02:07.170 --> 02:08.500
Chad, please pull up!

02:08.500 --> 02:10.670
[ Blaring continues ]

02:10.670 --> 02:12.790
♪♪

02:12.790 --> 02:14.330
Chad, pull up!

02:14.330 --> 02:15.420
Pull up! Pull up!

02:15.420 --> 02:17.000
Please, Chad, pull up!

02:17.000 --> 02:20.170
[ Gasping ]

02:20.170 --> 02:22.170
[ Breathing heavily ]

02:22.170 --> 02:23.500
[ Sighs ]

02:31.380 --> 02:34.670
♪♪

02:34.670 --> 02:36.290
[ Exhales sharply ]

02:36.290 --> 02:37.500
I love it.

02:37.500 --> 02:40.120
I love it even more
the second time.

02:40.120 --> 02:41.120
Built-ins, huh?

02:41.120 --> 02:42.290
Who doesn't love built-ins?

02:42.290 --> 02:43.500
Great poker face.

02:43.500 --> 02:45.670
You'll definitely be able
to negotiate the price.

02:45.670 --> 02:47.960
It's walking distance
to Theo's school.

02:47.960 --> 02:50.000
It's also walking distance
from the job you don't have.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.000
He's kidding.

02:51.000 --> 02:52.000
I teach guitar.

02:52.000 --> 02:52.960
Never here.

02:52.960 --> 02:54.330
I really don't care.

02:54.330 --> 02:57.040
I just care about your credit
score, which checked out.

02:57.040 --> 02:59.880
♪♪

02:59.880 --> 03:01.250
Okay, Gary,
what do you think?

03:01.250 --> 03:03.500
Should this be my room
or Theo's?

03:03.500 --> 03:04.920
[ Cellphone chimes ]

03:04.920 --> 03:07.080
Hey. Bud. Get off your phone.

03:07.080 --> 03:08.540
Dude, I'm blowing up
over here.

03:08.540 --> 03:09.710
I don't know
what to tell you, man.

03:09.710 --> 03:13.580
I'm back on the market,
and the ladies love to shop.

03:13.580 --> 03:15.210
Hello, Natasha.

03:15.210 --> 03:16.620
That's a lovely romper.

03:16.620 --> 03:18.670
Okay, you should be using
that phone to call Maggie.

03:18.670 --> 03:20.830
I told you I don't want
to talk about that.

03:20.830 --> 03:22.210
I do want to talk about Eva,

03:22.210 --> 03:24.040
'cause if she could only have
three things on a desert island,

03:24.040 --> 03:26.710
they would be vodka,
vermouth, and a shaker.

03:26.710 --> 03:29.330
Okay, this woman is telling you
she has a drinking problem.

03:29.330 --> 03:31.120
Oop. She also
has three kids.

03:31.120 --> 03:32.120
Maybe she's married.

03:32.120 --> 03:33.670
I'll earmark her for you.

03:33.670 --> 03:35.380
Agent: Things in
this neighborhood go fast.

03:35.380 --> 03:36.710
If you like it,
I would recommend

03:36.710 --> 03:38.500
you put down a deposit
as soon as possible.

03:38.500 --> 03:39.670
Couldn't agree more.

03:39.670 --> 03:42.330
Soon as you move out,
Commando Gary moves back in.

03:42.330 --> 03:45.830
What's the point of having a
suede couch if I can't feel it?

03:45.830 --> 03:47.580
Check okay?
Yeah.

03:47.580 --> 03:48.580
Here's the lease.

03:48.580 --> 03:50.210
It's a minimum
one-year commitment.

03:50.210 --> 03:51.500
[ Cellphone chimes ]

03:51.500 --> 03:53.040
Oh. One year.

03:53.040 --> 03:54.420
Standard.

03:54.420 --> 03:57.000
♪♪

03:57.000 --> 03:59.080
Gina, it smells so good.

03:59.080 --> 04:00.790
If I throw up,
just remember it's 'cause

04:00.790 --> 04:02.170
I have all-day morning sickness.

04:02.170 --> 04:03.580
Yeah, well,
if I throw up,

04:03.580 --> 04:06.380
it's because I'm in
a very vulnerable place.

04:06.380 --> 04:08.420
Restaurants live or die
by their menu.

04:08.420 --> 04:10.250
Limiting the vomit talk --
that might help.

04:10.250 --> 04:12.170
Babe, don't be worried.
That's why we're doing a small,

04:12.170 --> 04:13.750
intimate tasting
for close friends.

04:13.750 --> 04:14.960
It's just us.

04:14.960 --> 04:16.330
-Hey.
-Ash.

04:16.330 --> 04:17.500
Hey.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.040
I, uh, picked up
the rest of the linens.

04:19.040 --> 04:20.080
Oh, amazing.

04:20.080 --> 04:21.540
Thank you.

04:21.540 --> 04:23.620
Give me a few more days
for the loan.

04:23.620 --> 04:24.670
I'm trying to work on it.

04:24.670 --> 04:26.330
Okay, well,
I can always use

04:26.330 --> 04:27.960
some of
the life insurance money.

04:27.960 --> 04:29.670
Oh, no.
D, don't use that money.

04:29.670 --> 04:31.540
Why? I'm sure
John would want that.

04:31.540 --> 04:33.080
Anyways, Ashley's gonna
figure it out...
Yeah.

04:33.080 --> 04:35.830
...and we can just focus
on the party.

04:35.830 --> 04:37.580
So, are these three tables
enough? Who all's coming?

04:37.580 --> 04:39.580
You, Gina, Gary, me...

04:39.580 --> 04:42.330
Ashley, Eddie,
Katherine texted me a maybe.

04:42.330 --> 04:43.830
Which, given everything
that's happened,

04:43.830 --> 04:46.420
sounds like a very polite
"not in a million years."

04:46.420 --> 04:47.540
I'm not touching that.

04:47.540 --> 04:48.830
-Me neither.
-Uh, nope.

04:48.830 --> 04:51.000
What about Maggie?
You heard from Maggie?

04:51.000 --> 04:52.460
I called, but she hasn't
called me back.

04:52.460 --> 04:54.790
Maybe she thinks
she can't be friends with us

04:54.790 --> 04:56.000
'cause she and Gary
broke up.

04:56.000 --> 04:58.080
Doesn't she know
that compassionate doctor

04:58.080 --> 04:59.920
trumps bearded man-child
every time?

04:59.920 --> 05:01.080
[ Laughter ]

05:01.080 --> 05:02.710
What happened
with their breakup, anyway?

05:02.710 --> 05:03.710
Gary happened.

05:03.710 --> 05:04.750
-Oh. Yeah. Sure.
-Mm-hmm.

05:04.750 --> 05:06.420
How are you not
taking this apartment?

05:06.420 --> 05:07.710
I'm just not sure.

05:07.710 --> 05:10.040
I mean, the previous tenants
had cats.

05:10.040 --> 05:11.750
I'm gonna have to check
with Theo's allergist.

05:11.750 --> 05:13.670
You're gonna check with
an allergist about an apartment?

05:13.670 --> 05:16.920
Does that seem like a thing
that normal people do?

05:16.920 --> 05:18.830
You know, Theo's spent plenty
of nights here with Colin.

05:18.830 --> 05:19.830
He's always been fine.

05:19.830 --> 05:21.920
Colin's not a cat.
Colin's a dog.

05:21.920 --> 05:23.170
What's the one
that lays eggs?

05:23.170 --> 05:25.170
[ Chuckles ]
Speaking of chickens,

05:25.170 --> 05:27.670
are you afraid to commit
to a one-year lease?

05:27.670 --> 05:29.040
Me?

05:29.040 --> 05:32.000
You can't even make a commitment
to a three-week relationship.

05:32.000 --> 05:35.750
Gary, get off those dating apps
and call Maggie.

05:35.750 --> 05:38.000
Do not screw this one up
like you normally do.

05:38.000 --> 05:40.540
Trust me. You don't know
the whole story.

05:40.540 --> 05:42.250
Oh, and yet I do.

05:42.250 --> 05:45.000
Gary meets girl, Gary hooks up,
Gary gets bored.

05:45.000 --> 05:46.880
Man, I have seen
porn flicks

05:46.880 --> 05:48.880
with more plot twists
than your love life.

05:48.880 --> 05:50.580
You're watching porn
for the plot?

05:50.580 --> 05:52.960
[ Chuckles ]
Look, the point is, Gary,

05:52.960 --> 05:54.880
you find problems
with these women,

05:54.880 --> 05:57.170
but maybe
the problem's with you.

05:57.170 --> 05:58.830
Oh, says
the drunk adulterer

05:58.830 --> 06:00.880
living on
his best friend's futon.

06:01.830 --> 06:02.830
You know what, man?

06:02.830 --> 06:04.670
[ Clatter ]

06:04.670 --> 06:08.420
Maybe you should stop
taking shots at me

06:08.420 --> 06:11.000
and get Maggie back.

06:12.080 --> 06:14.620
Or is your plan
just to stand there

06:14.620 --> 06:17.170
and do nothing
and lose her forever?

06:17.170 --> 06:18.290
[ Sighs ]

06:18.290 --> 06:19.500
How about this, Ed?

06:19.500 --> 06:21.500
How about instead
of telling me what to do,

06:21.500 --> 06:23.210
try having my back?

06:23.210 --> 06:24.920
I'm the one
that gave you another chance

06:24.920 --> 06:26.170
after you screwed Delilah.

06:26.170 --> 06:28.830
I'm the one that took you in
after Katherine put you out.

06:28.830 --> 06:31.420
You're always so fast
to assume that it's my fault.

06:31.420 --> 06:33.580
Well, guess what --
you don't know!

06:33.580 --> 06:41.710
♪♪

06:41.710 --> 06:43.420
We need to look over
the findings

06:43.420 --> 06:45.290
of the environmental impact
report

06:45.290 --> 06:47.960
and finalize our list
of potential expert witnesses.

06:47.960 --> 06:50.500
Or we could sneak across
the street to the food court

06:50.500 --> 06:52.670
and stuff our faces
with cheese fries.

06:52.670 --> 06:53.880
Ah.

06:53.880 --> 06:56.120
It's hard to bill
for cheese fries.

06:56.120 --> 06:57.460
I mean, I've done it.

06:57.460 --> 06:58.500
Have you?

06:58.500 --> 07:00.250
No, I never
leave this building.

07:00.250 --> 07:02.790
Seriously. I mean,
why don't we go out sometime?

07:02.790 --> 07:04.670
Someplace fancier
than a noodle shop,

07:04.670 --> 07:08.080
and maybe we don't talk
about work.

07:08.080 --> 07:09.120
Oh.

07:09.120 --> 07:10.330
Look,
I know we're colleagues.

07:10.330 --> 07:12.170
No, uh, it's...

07:12.170 --> 07:13.380
[ Sighs ]

07:13.380 --> 07:15.460
It's -- It's not that.

07:16.830 --> 07:20.500
It's just -- with everything
with Eddie, and...

07:23.210 --> 07:24.210
I'm...

07:24.210 --> 07:26.500
You're not sure
if you're ready.

07:28.040 --> 07:30.540
I'm sure I'm not ready.

07:34.830 --> 07:36.830
Bruschetta it is.

07:37.830 --> 07:39.880
[ Indistinct conversation ]

07:46.880 --> 07:48.920
[ Sighs ]

07:56.960 --> 07:57.960
Hey.

07:59.170 --> 08:01.710
It's me.

08:01.710 --> 08:05.000
The jerk who dared you
to do chemo.

08:05.000 --> 08:06.880
That was dumb.

08:06.880 --> 08:09.170
If you're in there,
can we talk, please?

08:12.380 --> 08:14.170
Maybe you're not home.

08:16.380 --> 08:21.830
Maybe you are home
and don't want to talk to me,

08:21.830 --> 08:23.000
which clearly you don't.

08:23.000 --> 08:27.170
You haven't answered my calls
or my texts.

08:27.170 --> 08:29.210
But who's counting?

08:29.210 --> 08:31.250
I am. I'm counting.

08:31.250 --> 08:32.620
[ Chuckles ]

08:35.580 --> 08:39.000
I know I'm on record as saying
that emojis are stupid,

08:39.000 --> 08:43.880
but I'd be willing to accept
a flesh-toned thumbs up from you

08:43.880 --> 08:46.210
right about now.

08:46.210 --> 08:48.790
If you're in there, will you
just knock three times, please,

08:48.790 --> 08:52.500
so that I know
you're still...alive?

08:54.000 --> 08:55.750
Listen, I'm sorry.

08:57.540 --> 08:58.880
I tried.

09:01.080 --> 09:04.120
♪♪

09:04.120 --> 09:05.790
I can't not care.

09:05.790 --> 09:12.920
♪♪

09:12.920 --> 09:20.080
♪♪

09:20.080 --> 09:27.250
♪♪

09:31.330 --> 09:32.420
Hey, I'm at the pier.
I picked up lunch.

09:32.420 --> 09:33.620
I got your salad
with extra dressing

09:33.620 --> 09:35.830
because I now know
that lettuce without dressing

09:35.830 --> 09:37.040
is just garnish.

09:37.040 --> 09:39.540
I am learning so much
at these sessions.

09:39.540 --> 09:42.040
[ Chuckles ] I'm sorry
to do this last minute,

09:42.040 --> 09:44.790
but I can't make it today.

09:44.790 --> 09:45.880
Okay.

09:47.380 --> 09:48.580
But now
I'm just standing here

09:48.580 --> 09:50.920
with a ridiculous amount
of buttermilk ranch,

09:50.920 --> 09:54.380
which, if I may counsel you,
does not go well with Nicoise.

09:54.380 --> 09:56.830
Uh, the thing is,
Rome, um...

09:56.830 --> 10:00.670
I can't meet with you anymore
at all.

10:00.670 --> 10:02.000
Because of Gary?

10:02.000 --> 10:04.420
So, w-what, at first,

10:04.420 --> 10:06.670
you couldn't be my non-therapist
because you were dating,

10:06.670 --> 10:08.170
and now you can't be
my non-therapist

10:08.170 --> 10:09.210
because you broke up?

10:09.210 --> 10:12.000
No, this has nothing to do
with Gary.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.500
Then I don't get it.

10:14.500 --> 10:16.170
Just when I start
feeling better,

10:16.170 --> 10:18.040
that's when
you pull the rug out?

10:18.040 --> 10:19.790
What's going on, Maggie?

10:19.790 --> 10:23.460
Uh, look, you're in good hands
with Dr. Heller,

10:23.460 --> 10:25.080
and you're making
great progress,

10:25.080 --> 10:29.040
and I'm gonna send you referrals
to another psychologist.

10:29.040 --> 10:30.120
[ Sighs ]

10:30.120 --> 10:32.710
♪♪

10:32.710 --> 10:35.420
I'm -- I'm so sorry, Rome.

10:35.420 --> 10:36.710
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:36.710 --> 10:38.830
♪♪

10:38.830 --> 10:40.460
Eddie: Your kind of
run-of-the-mill bathroom,

10:40.460 --> 10:41.670
claw-foot tub.

10:41.670 --> 10:43.000
Check this out.

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
This here
would be Theo's bedroom

10:45.000 --> 10:47.500
with his own
dedicated closet.

10:47.500 --> 10:49.210
Hardwood floors --
look at that.

10:49.210 --> 10:51.460
Eddie, you don't have to
show me all this.

10:51.460 --> 10:52.670
It's your place.

10:52.670 --> 10:54.120
Oh, I want to.

10:55.830 --> 11:03.210
Look, I've, uh, made
so many missteps with you.

11:03.210 --> 11:05.210
I don't want to make
any more mistakes.

11:06.920 --> 11:10.000
Anyway, they, um --
they want a year lease,

11:10.000 --> 11:12.040
and I didn't want
to make any decisions

11:12.040 --> 11:15.960
till I talked with you
about, you know...

11:15.960 --> 11:17.330
where we are.

11:19.330 --> 11:21.290
Ah.

11:21.290 --> 11:22.920
Gary told you,
didn't he?

11:22.920 --> 11:25.330
Look, it was just a work dinner.
It wasn't a date.

11:26.790 --> 11:28.790
What are we
talking about?

11:28.790 --> 11:30.420
Let's not do this.

11:30.420 --> 11:32.500
Gary obviously told you
he saw me with Hunter

11:32.500 --> 11:34.670
at the noodle shop.

11:34.670 --> 11:37.250
[ Sighs ]

11:37.250 --> 11:38.960
Gary didn't say anything
to me.

11:38.960 --> 11:41.830
Definitely didn't mention
anyone named Hunter.

11:41.830 --> 11:43.290
Sorry, is that
his given name?

11:43.290 --> 11:45.670
He's an attorney.
We're on a case together.

11:45.670 --> 11:47.710
The hearing got moved up,
so we're putting in long hours.

11:47.710 --> 11:50.500
Look, it's strictly
professional, nothing more.

11:50.500 --> 11:52.170
Well, you don't
have to explain.

11:57.420 --> 11:58.500
Katherine.

12:00.540 --> 12:05.170
Even if it were more,

12:05.170 --> 12:08.000
I would be happy for you.

12:08.000 --> 12:12.330
Not that you need my permission,
but you deserve to be happy.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.080
[ Sighs ]

12:16.080 --> 12:18.170
Thanks.

12:18.170 --> 12:21.540
♪♪

12:21.540 --> 12:23.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:26.170 --> 12:27.420
Come in.

12:32.040 --> 12:34.000
I-I thought, uh...

12:35.500 --> 12:36.620
Where's Maggie?

12:36.620 --> 12:39.790
Oh. Um, Dr. Bloom
doesn't work here anymore.

12:39.790 --> 12:41.670
They told me she tried to reach
out to all of her patients

12:41.670 --> 12:43.380
before she left.
[ Exhales shakily ]

12:43.380 --> 12:45.580
Do you need a referral?

12:45.580 --> 12:46.880
Sir?

12:50.250 --> 12:53.210
[ Knock on door ]

12:53.210 --> 12:55.670
Look, I'm sorry
to make you come back,

12:55.670 --> 12:58.790
but if you had just bought the
extra dressing the first time,

12:58.790 --> 13:02.000
we would not be
in this situation.

13:02.000 --> 13:03.420
We need to talk.

13:03.420 --> 13:05.290
Gina,
you don't understand.

13:05.290 --> 13:07.540
No, I don't understand.

13:07.540 --> 13:09.830
My husband turned to you
in his darkest hour,

13:09.830 --> 13:12.670
and you agreed to see him,
and now that he depends on you,

13:12.670 --> 13:13.750
you cut bait?

13:13.750 --> 13:15.500
No, that's not
what I am doing at all.

13:15.500 --> 13:17.500
I gave him the name
of three therapists

13:17.500 --> 13:18.500
who are excellent --
No.

13:18.500 --> 13:20.460
No, he trusts you.

13:20.460 --> 13:21.620
And so do I.

13:23.040 --> 13:25.710
That's --
That's a problem.

13:25.710 --> 13:27.460
That is it.
I can't --

13:27.460 --> 13:29.670
I know both of you,
and as a therapist,

13:29.670 --> 13:33.920
I have to establish boundaries,
which means no friendships.

13:33.920 --> 13:36.710
Oh, I refuse
to accept that.

13:36.710 --> 13:37.830
You give me
one good reason

13:37.830 --> 13:39.580
why you can't keep seeing
my husband.

13:42.170 --> 13:44.290
[ Sighs ]
Because I'm dying.

13:45.580 --> 13:47.170
W-What?

13:47.170 --> 13:52.460
♪♪

13:52.460 --> 13:54.170
[ Sighs ]

13:54.170 --> 14:03.500
♪♪

14:03.500 --> 14:06.420
Hey, you're Maggie's friend.
I'm Tom.

14:06.420 --> 14:08.120
I'm Gary.
Nice to meet you.

14:08.120 --> 14:16.170
♪♪

14:16.170 --> 14:17.540
Take me to the airport, please.

14:17.540 --> 14:19.080
Okay, get in.

14:21.330 --> 14:22.710
[ Sighs ]

14:28.420 --> 14:29.830
She didn't tell us because
she was afraid we were gonna

14:29.830 --> 14:32.120
treat her like "cancer girl" and
push her into getting treatment.

14:32.120 --> 14:33.830
We should push her
into getting treatment.

14:33.830 --> 14:34.830
No.

14:36.080 --> 14:38.000
It's why
she and Gary broke up.

14:39.830 --> 14:41.540
We all blamed Gary.

14:43.670 --> 14:45.380
He was just
protecting her secret.

14:46.830 --> 14:50.380
She shouldn't be pushing us away
when she needs us most.

14:50.380 --> 14:52.380
No, she shouldn't.

14:52.380 --> 14:53.880
We're not gonna let her.

14:56.080 --> 14:58.500
♪ Have you ever loved someone? ♪

14:58.500 --> 15:01.210
♪ You just give them
all that they want ♪

15:01.210 --> 15:03.670
♪ I just wanna hold you tight ♪

15:03.670 --> 15:07.250
♪ Even if it's just
for one night ♪

15:07.250 --> 15:09.500
Hi!
Hi, this is...

15:09.500 --> 15:12.330
Hey, sorry for the impromptu
visit. We just came to --

15:12.330 --> 15:14.960
I know
why you're all here.

15:14.960 --> 15:18.670
This is, uh, the part where you
give me the big speech, right?

15:18.670 --> 15:19.790
"Don't give up, Maggie!

15:19.790 --> 15:22.170
Get treatment.
Choose life."

15:22.170 --> 15:24.290
I've already thought this
through, and I made up my mind.

15:24.290 --> 15:27.290
Yeah, uh,
w-we didn't come to do that.

15:27.290 --> 15:28.750
-No.
-No?

15:28.750 --> 15:31.500
No, no, we came because we need
help picking out the wine

15:31.500 --> 15:33.830
for tomorrow night's party,
and I'm not drinking,

15:33.830 --> 15:35.380
and I don't trust
his taste, so...

15:35.380 --> 15:36.790
[ Laughter ]

15:36.790 --> 15:40.250
Look, we got a case of wine,
and an assortment of cheese.

15:40.250 --> 15:41.420
Yeah,
and let's be honest.

15:41.420 --> 15:43.170
We bought the cheese
so we wouldn't feel as bad

15:43.170 --> 15:44.170
about the day-drinking.

15:44.170 --> 15:45.500
-That is true.
-Mm-hmm.

15:45.500 --> 15:47.580
Gina: Oh, and bread --
we did not bring bread.

15:47.580 --> 15:48.710
Do you have bread?

15:48.710 --> 15:49.830
I do.

15:51.460 --> 15:52.580
All right, come on in.

15:52.580 --> 15:53.580
Okay.

15:53.580 --> 15:55.120
[ Laughter ]

15:55.120 --> 16:03.920
♪♪

16:03.920 --> 16:05.170
Oh! Tom!

16:05.170 --> 16:06.750
Tom.

16:06.750 --> 16:08.080
Hey.
[ Chuckling ] Hey!

16:08.080 --> 16:10.750
You're Maggie's friend,
uh, uh, Gary, right?

16:10.750 --> 16:11.670
Yeah.

16:11.670 --> 16:13.920
Yeah, what are you doing
in Chi--

16:13.920 --> 16:15.710
Oh, my God.
No, no, no. No.

16:15.710 --> 16:17.040
She's alive.

16:18.880 --> 16:21.080
Can I -- [ Sighs ]
Can I walk with you?

16:21.080 --> 16:22.120
Yeah, yeah.

16:25.750 --> 16:26.920
Eddie:
This is fantastic.

16:26.920 --> 16:28.080
He didn't have a key
or anything,

16:28.080 --> 16:29.330
yet he got back inside.

16:29.330 --> 16:30.880
Theo:
Or maybe he snuck in.

16:30.880 --> 16:32.620
You know what he did?
He's very tiny.

16:32.620 --> 16:35.000
I think the moral
of the story, though, is that

16:35.000 --> 16:38.540
even though Curious George
moved to a new place,

16:38.540 --> 16:43.670
he was comfortable
living in a new city.

16:43.670 --> 16:46.420
That George,
he's very curious.

16:46.420 --> 16:47.880
Look at that.

16:47.880 --> 16:49.500
I don't think so.
Hmm?

16:49.500 --> 16:52.380
'Cause if he were,
he wouldn't call his friend

16:52.380 --> 16:54.670
"The Man
In The Yellow Hat."

16:54.670 --> 16:58.170
He'd say,
"Hey, what's your name?

16:58.170 --> 17:00.000
Just curious."

17:00.000 --> 17:01.460
That's a very good point.

17:01.460 --> 17:03.170
I'll add it
to our list of letters.

17:03.170 --> 17:05.540
Actually,
you know what, bud?

17:05.540 --> 17:08.500
I, um, I wanted to talk to you
about something.

17:08.500 --> 17:11.000
Uh-oh. That's
your serious voice.

17:11.000 --> 17:13.250
No, it is not serious
at all.

17:13.250 --> 17:14.960
This is actually
really good news.

17:14.960 --> 17:19.000
You and I
are gonna be moving.

17:19.000 --> 17:21.170
We are?
Mm-hmm!

17:21.170 --> 17:23.500
Does Mommy know
we're coming home?

17:23.500 --> 17:25.920
♪♪

17:25.920 --> 17:30.920
No -- [ Chuckles ]
Bud.

17:30.920 --> 17:33.460
We're not gonna be moving in
with Mommy.

17:33.460 --> 17:35.710
Daddy is getting
his own apartment.

17:35.710 --> 17:38.540
Our own apartment.

17:38.540 --> 17:41.880
Does Uncle Gary
not want us here anymore?

17:41.880 --> 17:45.670
No, buddy,
Uncle Gary loves you.

17:45.670 --> 17:48.000
In fact, he made me promise
that he can come over

17:48.000 --> 17:49.580
and visit
anytime he wants.

17:49.580 --> 17:51.500
Then where is he?

17:51.500 --> 17:52.580
We were supposed to wrestle

17:52.580 --> 17:54.380
for the Championship
of the World tonight.

17:54.380 --> 17:55.500
That was tonight?

17:55.500 --> 17:56.750
Yes, tonight.

17:56.750 --> 18:01.620
Well, he's clearly forfeiting
because he's a chicken.

18:01.620 --> 18:05.500
And we all know
what you do with chickens!

18:05.500 --> 18:06.710
Turn 'em into nuggets!

18:06.710 --> 18:09.120
Ah, boof, boof!
[ Laughing ]

18:09.120 --> 18:11.000
[ Grunting ]

18:11.000 --> 18:12.210
One for you.

18:12.210 --> 18:13.960
-Mmm. Thank you.
-One for you.

18:13.960 --> 18:15.830
Still none for you.

18:15.830 --> 18:18.210
I'm a French woman
near soft cheese and wine.

18:18.210 --> 18:20.080
It's just not fair!

18:20.080 --> 18:21.620
Why do you have
all the moving boxes?

18:21.620 --> 18:23.380
Oh, I'm just putting some stuff
in storage.

18:23.380 --> 18:27.080
[ Sniffs ] This is, um,
medium bodied, complex, dry...

18:27.080 --> 18:28.000
Mm-hmm.

18:28.000 --> 18:29.790
With, like,
hints of gooseberry.

18:29.790 --> 18:31.080
-Gooseberry.
-Mm-hmm.

18:31.080 --> 18:32.670
You just making up food names
now, Maggie?

18:32.670 --> 18:34.170
[ Laughter ]
You know what?

18:34.170 --> 18:36.290
Hands down, I would pair
the Sauvignon Blanc

18:36.290 --> 18:37.620
with the scallops.

18:37.620 --> 18:39.210
Great. Can we move on
to the reds?

18:39.210 --> 18:40.250
-Mm-hmm.
-No, wait.

18:40.250 --> 18:41.500
I can't move on
until I figure out

18:41.500 --> 18:43.210
what a gooseberry is,
seriously.

18:43.210 --> 18:44.380
[ Laughter ]

18:44.380 --> 18:46.670
Delilah: Gooseberry is
a green and fuzzy fruit.

18:46.670 --> 18:48.670
Wait, "goose" --
does it come from a goose?

18:48.670 --> 18:50.880
Oh, my God,
Maggie, what's happening?

18:50.880 --> 18:52.710
Hey.

18:52.710 --> 18:54.000
[ Sniffles, shudders ]

18:54.000 --> 18:55.790
No, it's just...

18:55.790 --> 18:57.790
we've been talking about wine
for two hours,

18:57.790 --> 18:59.460
and you haven't
brought it up once.

18:59.460 --> 19:00.790
We thought
that's what you wanted.

19:00.790 --> 19:04.120
No, it's good. It's good.
I do. I just...

19:04.120 --> 19:06.460
[ Sighs ]
This wasn't supposed to happen.

19:06.460 --> 19:08.000
Yeah, sweetie, I know.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.170
Cancer sucks.

19:09.170 --> 19:10.880
Not the cancer.

19:10.880 --> 19:13.250
♪♪

19:13.250 --> 19:17.040
[ Voice breaking ] This.
This wasn't supposed to happen.

19:17.040 --> 19:19.500
I was just supposed to go
to a support group

19:19.500 --> 19:22.250
and live my life to the fullest
until I couldn't,

19:22.250 --> 19:23.960
and then I met Gary.

19:23.960 --> 19:25.250
I just didn't -- [ Laughs ]

19:25.250 --> 19:27.880
I didn't think that a guy
that I hooked up with

19:27.880 --> 19:30.670
in a church bathroom
would lead me to friends

19:30.670 --> 19:34.500
who would support me
in living the rest of my life

19:34.500 --> 19:35.920
the way that I want
to live it.

19:35.920 --> 19:37.330
[ Sniffles ]

19:37.330 --> 19:39.830
Then why are you
pushing us away?

19:39.830 --> 19:42.670
Because I can't do this.

19:42.670 --> 19:44.750
I can't --
I can't hurt you.

19:44.750 --> 19:47.000
Listen,
you get to choose

19:47.000 --> 19:48.420
whether or not
you want to do chemo,

19:48.420 --> 19:49.620
but you don't
get to choose

19:49.620 --> 19:51.000
whether or not
we're here for you.

19:51.000 --> 19:53.000
Yeah,
we -- we choose that,

19:53.000 --> 19:54.080
'cause we're your friends,

19:54.080 --> 19:56.500
and that's just the price
of admission.

19:56.500 --> 19:59.920
♪♪

19:59.920 --> 20:03.500
Yeah. Yeah, I lost someone, um,
[Sniffles] a while ago,

20:03.500 --> 20:06.330
and it...

20:06.330 --> 20:10.250
someone I tried to save,
and it still really hurts.

20:10.250 --> 20:12.170
[ Sniffles ]

20:12.170 --> 20:15.670
And I can't put anyone
through that kind of pain.

20:17.750 --> 20:20.580
You think I don't
feel that pain every day?

20:20.580 --> 20:24.330
That's --
That's what friends do.

20:24.330 --> 20:27.540
The night I met you,
you held my hand when --

20:27.540 --> 20:28.710
when I buried my husband.

20:28.710 --> 20:31.040
And that's exactly
why I can't bear the thought

20:31.040 --> 20:33.420
of you
being at my funeral.

20:33.420 --> 20:41.250
♪♪

20:41.250 --> 20:42.420
[ Sighs ]

20:42.420 --> 20:43.670
She won't
talk to me, man.

20:43.670 --> 20:47.500
I can't even get her
to open the door.

20:47.500 --> 20:50.830
I need you to help me
knock down that door

20:50.830 --> 20:52.500
and get her
back to chemo.

20:52.500 --> 20:54.460
It's not gonna happen,
man.

20:54.460 --> 20:56.000
That door
is not coming down,

20:56.000 --> 20:59.120
and there is nothing
that you or I can do about it.

20:59.120 --> 21:01.830
It was put up long before
you and I even met her

21:01.830 --> 21:03.000
by some guy
named Chad.

21:03.000 --> 21:04.000
Chad?
Yeah.

21:04.000 --> 21:05.120
No, I've never --

21:05.120 --> 21:07.080
Yeah, well,
she doesn't talk about him.

21:07.080 --> 21:08.880
[ Sighs ]
Believe me, I've tried.

21:08.880 --> 21:12.880
He...did a number
on her.

21:12.880 --> 21:14.250
[ Sighs ]

21:17.580 --> 21:19.460
So, what do we do, man?
T-That's it?

21:19.460 --> 21:21.460
So, what?
We give up?

21:21.460 --> 21:25.670
I had a psych professor
in grad school

21:25.670 --> 21:30.380
who used to say,
"You can't save someone

21:30.380 --> 21:32.210
if they don't want
to save themselves."

21:32.210 --> 21:33.460
Yeah, I've heard that.
You know what?

21:33.460 --> 21:35.750
I lost my best friend
recently,

21:35.750 --> 21:40.170
and there's not a day that
goes by where I don't wonder

21:40.170 --> 21:43.120
if there was something
I could've done to save him.

21:43.120 --> 21:46.330
That's why I'm here.
It's very simple.

21:46.330 --> 21:50.580
I need to know I did
everything I could to save her.

21:50.580 --> 21:53.460
So I'm asking you.

21:53.460 --> 21:57.830
Please, Tom,
get on a plane.

21:59.210 --> 22:01.580
Come back with me
to Boston.

22:03.170 --> 22:06.210
The thing is,
I already flew to Boston

22:06.210 --> 22:07.830
to try
to convince her.

22:10.460 --> 22:12.920
I can't do
that flight home again.

22:12.920 --> 22:18.000
♪♪

22:18.000 --> 22:23.290
♪ Whenever I'm alone with you ♪

22:23.290 --> 22:25.670
[ Rumbling ]

22:25.670 --> 22:27.040
[ Switch clicks ]

22:27.040 --> 22:28.670
Why are you switching it
off auto-pilot?

22:28.670 --> 22:31.790
Because we're not headed
in the direction I want to go.

22:31.790 --> 22:35.830
Okay, it's gonna be harder
than you thought.

22:35.830 --> 22:37.580
[ Rumbling ]
Oh, my God.

22:37.580 --> 22:38.920
My airspeed's dropping.
[ Engine revving ]

22:38.920 --> 22:40.080
[ Alarm blaring ]
Oh, my God.

22:40.080 --> 22:41.460
Just keep your eyes
on the horizon.

22:41.460 --> 22:43.000
Pull up. Pull up.

22:43.000 --> 22:44.210
Switch it back
to auto-pilot.

22:44.210 --> 22:45.420
No.

22:45.420 --> 22:46.420
No!

22:46.420 --> 22:48.250
[ Blaring continues ]

22:48.250 --> 22:49.540
What are you doing here?

22:49.540 --> 22:50.960
Rome, you shouldn't be here.
It's only gonna get worse.

22:50.960 --> 22:52.000
I got you.

22:52.000 --> 22:53.500
[ Gasps ]

22:53.500 --> 22:55.670
Pull up. Pull up.
I don't want you
to get hurt.

22:55.670 --> 22:57.920
We are in this together.

22:57.920 --> 22:59.670
[ Gasps ]

22:59.670 --> 23:02.380
[ Breathing heavily ]

23:13.120 --> 23:14.790
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

23:14.790 --> 23:15.880
[ Cellphone beeps ]

23:15.880 --> 23:18.330
Eddie?
Everything okay?

23:18.330 --> 23:19.540
No, it's not.

23:19.540 --> 23:21.290
Have you heard from Gary?

23:21.290 --> 23:22.710
No, why?

23:22.710 --> 23:24.290
Well, he didn't come home
last night.

23:24.290 --> 23:26.040
He's not answering
any of my texts.

23:26.040 --> 23:28.250
I'm supposed to make the final
decision on my apartment today,

23:28.250 --> 23:30.290
but I had to walk his dog
three times.

23:30.290 --> 23:32.000
Without getting
too graphic, D,

23:32.000 --> 23:35.210
Colin's poops are proportionate
to the size of his body,

23:35.210 --> 23:37.000
and his body is the size
of a small horse.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.330
Okay, slow down. Stop.
What -- What...

23:39.330 --> 23:41.420
I tried to apologize
for this little fight, but...

23:41.420 --> 23:42.670
What'd you guys
fight about?

23:42.670 --> 23:46.170
I told him he was being an idiot
for losing Maggie,

23:46.170 --> 23:47.880
that she's the best woman
he's ever dated.

23:47.880 --> 23:50.080
[ Groans ]

23:50.080 --> 23:52.420
Eddie, there's, uh...

23:55.120 --> 23:56.380
Where are you?

23:56.380 --> 23:58.460
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

24:00.960 --> 24:02.920
[ Cellphone beeps ]

24:02.920 --> 24:03.710
Hello?

24:03.710 --> 24:05.500
Hey.

24:05.500 --> 24:08.210
I-I know you're probably
not going to,

24:08.210 --> 24:11.040
but I just wanted
to call and tell you

24:11.040 --> 24:14.000
how much Delilah and I
want you at the party tonight.

24:14.000 --> 24:18.500
Just promise me
you'll think about it.

24:18.500 --> 24:19.880
I'll think about it.

24:19.880 --> 24:21.670
That's all I'm asking.
[ Chuckles ]

24:21.670 --> 24:23.620
Just think about it...

24:23.620 --> 24:25.710
in the car...
on the ride over.

24:25.710 --> 24:26.710
[ Chuckles ]

24:26.710 --> 24:28.670
Okay.

24:28.670 --> 24:29.920
[ Cellphone beeps ]

24:29.920 --> 24:36.670
♪♪

24:36.670 --> 24:42.880
♪♪

24:42.880 --> 24:44.170
Everything okay?

24:44.170 --> 24:45.170
Yeah.

24:45.170 --> 24:46.790
You sure?

24:46.790 --> 24:47.670
Yeah.

24:48.960 --> 24:50.000
[ Clears throat ]

24:50.000 --> 24:51.420
What are you doing
tonight?

24:54.080 --> 24:55.750
You tell me.

24:55.750 --> 24:59.750
♪♪

24:59.750 --> 25:01.790
Ugh. I feel like
such an ass.

25:03.620 --> 25:04.790
[ Sighs ]

25:04.790 --> 25:06.710
Why didn't Gary
say anything?

25:09.380 --> 25:11.670
Maggie didn't want
anyone to know.

25:14.170 --> 25:15.420
How long?

25:17.290 --> 25:18.380
[ Sighs ]

25:18.380 --> 25:20.670
Less than a year.

25:20.670 --> 25:24.120
[ Exhales sharply ]

25:24.120 --> 25:29.210
God, you think you have
your whole life ahead of you...

25:29.210 --> 25:31.960
Then you go
for a cup of coffee...

25:31.960 --> 25:35.120
♪♪

25:35.120 --> 25:36.880
...everything changes.

25:40.000 --> 25:42.250
This is really nice.

25:42.250 --> 25:43.290
Thanks.

25:45.580 --> 25:50.120
I always thought the next
apartment I would rent

25:50.120 --> 25:51.830
would be for us.

25:53.710 --> 25:56.670
I can't --
I can't lose anyone else.

25:59.380 --> 26:01.040
It's okay.

26:01.040 --> 26:10.000
♪♪

26:10.000 --> 26:18.830
♪♪

26:18.830 --> 26:27.750
♪♪

26:27.750 --> 26:29.080
No.

26:29.080 --> 26:30.540
♪♪

26:30.540 --> 26:33.290
[ Sniffles ]

26:33.290 --> 26:35.330
No, no, no.
We can't. Not --

26:35.330 --> 26:36.960
No matter
how much I want to.

26:39.540 --> 26:42.210
Not if we're saying
that our --

26:42.210 --> 26:44.210
that this baby is Jon's.

26:44.210 --> 26:47.500
♪♪

26:47.500 --> 26:48.790
[ Exhales shakily ]

26:50.080 --> 26:51.920
[ Knock on door ]

27:02.500 --> 27:04.380
Not saying I don't
love the sweatpants
with the holes in them,

27:04.380 --> 27:05.670
but you might be
a little underdressed

27:05.670 --> 27:07.580
for this tasting party.

27:07.580 --> 27:09.750
What's with
all the boxes?

27:09.750 --> 27:12.500
I told you. I'm just putting
some stuff in storage.

27:12.500 --> 27:15.790
Yeah, I didn't buy it the first
time you said it, either.

27:15.790 --> 27:17.120
Can you tell me
the truth?

27:17.120 --> 27:19.500
[ Sighs ]

27:19.500 --> 27:21.710
Um, well,

27:21.710 --> 27:23.620
I don't want
my mom and dad

27:23.620 --> 27:25.250
to have to pack up
after I'm gone,

27:25.250 --> 27:28.380
so I'm doing it now
while I still can.

27:37.330 --> 27:38.880
What about the party?

27:38.880 --> 27:40.210
The party can wait.

27:52.500 --> 27:56.750
Last night, you mentioned
someone that you lost,

27:56.750 --> 27:58.040
someone you couldn't save.

28:00.330 --> 28:04.620
I just want you to know,
whoever it was,

28:04.620 --> 28:07.290
you might not have been able
to save them,

28:07.290 --> 28:09.750
but you sure as hell
saved me.

28:09.750 --> 28:17.040
♪♪

28:21.250 --> 28:24.040
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

28:24.040 --> 28:25.250
Hmm.

28:25.250 --> 28:29.540
♪♪

28:29.540 --> 28:30.330
Mmm.

28:30.330 --> 28:32.500
Uh, excuse me.

28:32.500 --> 28:36.670
Regina, I am crazy
for this Caprese.

28:36.670 --> 28:39.250
And this truffle mac --
totally whack.

28:39.250 --> 28:41.920
It amazes me that you convinced
two women to sleep with you.

28:41.920 --> 28:45.000
♪♪

28:45.000 --> 28:47.420
[ Sighs ]
She's not coming?

28:47.420 --> 28:49.620
Here's the thing,
you know...

28:49.620 --> 28:51.330
[ Laughing ] She is.

28:51.330 --> 28:52.380
Ta-da!

28:52.380 --> 28:54.620
[ Cheering ]

28:55.580 --> 28:56.920
Aaaah!

28:56.920 --> 28:58.170
So glad you came.

28:58.170 --> 28:59.880
Me too.

28:59.880 --> 29:02.170
Hi.

29:02.170 --> 29:03.710
Mag. Welcome.
Hey.

29:03.710 --> 29:04.670
Thank you.

29:04.670 --> 29:06.250
And let the tasting
begin.

29:06.250 --> 29:07.710
All right.

29:07.710 --> 29:11.750
Please, do not forget to share
your thoughts on the scallops.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.000
Be brutal.

29:13.000 --> 29:15.290
But not the mean brutal --
the nice brutal.

29:15.290 --> 29:18.000
[ Bill Withers' "Lovely Day"
plays ]

29:18.000 --> 29:20.670
Oh, hi, Katherine!
You made it!

29:20.670 --> 29:21.670
Katherine: Hey.

29:21.670 --> 29:23.500
Check out her plus-one.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.120
This is my friend Hunter.

29:25.120 --> 29:26.880
Yes, it is. [ Laughs ]

29:26.880 --> 29:28.040
It's nice to meet you.

29:28.040 --> 29:29.080
Hi. Regina.

29:30.210 --> 29:31.620
Hi.

29:31.620 --> 29:32.830
Hi, I'm Delilah.

29:34.120 --> 29:36.790
Thank you, Katherine,
for coming.

29:36.790 --> 29:38.170
Can I get you
a glass of wine?

29:39.620 --> 29:41.210
[ Chuckles ]

29:41.210 --> 29:43.830
Delicious, delicious.

29:43.830 --> 29:44.880
That man is delicious.

29:44.880 --> 29:46.040
That is not funny.

29:46.040 --> 29:47.710
He's like
a chocolate George Clooney

29:47.710 --> 29:49.750
with a caramel
Gosling center.

29:49.750 --> 29:52.250
Okay, he's just some guy
who works at her firm.

29:52.250 --> 29:54.670
Yes, everything about him
does seem firm.

29:54.670 --> 29:55.620
Bring it.

29:55.620 --> 29:56.830
You're not getting to me.

29:56.830 --> 29:58.670
Look at you
being the bigger man.

29:58.670 --> 29:59.960
I mean,
smaller bigger man.

29:59.960 --> 30:00.830
That's --

30:00.830 --> 30:01.830
He's taller.
I get it.

30:01.830 --> 30:03.330
That is hilarious.

30:03.330 --> 30:06.710
♪♪

30:06.710 --> 30:09.290
Seriously, man.

30:09.290 --> 30:11.330
How you doing
with all this, Ed?

30:13.290 --> 30:15.330
Well, you get
what you deserve.

30:17.880 --> 30:19.500
And I deserve this.

30:22.830 --> 30:23.830
Well...

30:23.830 --> 30:25.620
Hey, guys.

30:25.620 --> 30:27.250
Eddie.

30:27.250 --> 30:29.880
This is Hunter.

30:29.880 --> 30:31.330
Hey, man.
Nice to meet you.

30:31.330 --> 30:32.880
Nice to meet you.

30:32.880 --> 30:35.210
Guys, I highly recommend
the crab cakes.

30:35.210 --> 30:38.330
I'm gonna go
try those -- now.

30:38.330 --> 30:42.540
♪♪

30:42.540 --> 30:43.460
Hey.

30:45.080 --> 30:45.920
Hey.

30:45.920 --> 30:48.380
Can we talk?

30:48.380 --> 30:49.830
Uh, depends.

30:49.830 --> 30:52.120
Are you gonna
get treatment?

30:52.120 --> 30:55.580
Gary, do we really need
to rehash this right now?

30:55.580 --> 30:57.790
Nope.

30:57.790 --> 31:00.170
'Cause I'm not gonna care more
about your life than you do.

31:00.170 --> 31:05.120
♪♪

31:05.120 --> 31:06.540
Hey, Mama.

31:06.540 --> 31:07.790
Ohhhh!

31:07.790 --> 31:08.920
Hug this body.

31:08.920 --> 31:10.210
What's in my mouth?

31:10.210 --> 31:12.580
Good food.
It's so good!

31:12.580 --> 31:13.580
Hey, scarf.

31:13.580 --> 31:14.830
Hey, sneaks.

31:14.830 --> 31:16.040
See you also dressed up.

31:16.040 --> 31:17.210
It's a long story.

31:18.880 --> 31:23.170
Hey, I am so sorry.

31:23.170 --> 31:25.500
I said a bunch of things
I shouldn't have.

31:25.500 --> 31:27.500
I'm gonna give you guys
a minute.

31:27.500 --> 31:29.710
And they were
probably stupid.

31:29.710 --> 31:31.380
And, you know,
you're right.

31:31.380 --> 31:33.040
I probably didn't know
the whole story.

31:33.040 --> 31:35.080
Let's be honest -- even if
you had known the whole story,

31:35.080 --> 31:36.620
you still would've said
stupid things, Ed.

31:36.620 --> 31:37.830
That is your default.

31:37.830 --> 31:40.000
That's fair.
[ Chuckles ]

31:40.000 --> 31:42.000
And I will take
your apology.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.290
How's the apartment hunt
going?

31:43.290 --> 31:45.210
Did you get the approval
from your allergist?

31:45.210 --> 31:46.830
[ Chuckles ]
I haven't gotten that far.

31:46.830 --> 31:48.920
It's hard to sign
a year lease

31:48.920 --> 31:52.670
when you're still kind of living
kind of day-to-day.

31:52.670 --> 31:54.080
Here's an idea.

31:54.080 --> 31:56.830
Why don't you live
day-to-day with me

31:56.830 --> 31:58.120
for as long
as you need to?

31:58.120 --> 32:01.000
Not because
I would miss you.

32:01.000 --> 32:04.170
I would miss
that adorable Asian kid

32:04.170 --> 32:05.790
you keep insisting
is yours.

32:05.790 --> 32:07.540
[ Cellphone ringing ]

32:07.540 --> 32:09.620
[ Chuckles ]
What is this?

32:09.620 --> 32:11.120
What's happening tonight?

32:11.120 --> 32:12.290
Yo. Where are you?

32:12.290 --> 32:13.540
Maggie: Hey, sorry,

32:13.540 --> 32:17.290
but you wouldn't talk to me
any other way, so...

32:17.290 --> 32:19.670
♪♪

32:19.670 --> 32:21.830
[ Sighs ]
I owe you an apology.

32:21.830 --> 32:22.920
I'm listening.

32:22.920 --> 32:27.960
It was unfair
to let you get close to me.

32:29.120 --> 32:31.080
No.

32:31.080 --> 32:33.620
[ Sighs ] What isn't fair
is this choice

32:33.620 --> 32:37.120
that you have made
to not fight this.

32:39.420 --> 32:41.120
I understand
why you feel that way.

32:41.120 --> 32:43.170
Don't make it seem like
I'm the weirdo here, okay?

32:43.170 --> 32:45.420
I'm not unusual.

32:45.420 --> 32:50.000
If any of these other people
knew what I know, trust me,

32:50.000 --> 32:53.170
they would want you
to get treatment, Maggie.

32:53.170 --> 32:55.620
Gary, they do know.

32:55.620 --> 32:59.460
And they all support
my decision.

32:59.460 --> 33:02.170
What do you -- What?
What do you mean they know?

33:02.170 --> 33:07.830
♪♪

33:07.830 --> 33:09.210
No, wait, no.
Timeout.

33:09.210 --> 33:11.580
What? No way.
You guys can't be serious.

33:11.580 --> 33:12.830
Are we really just
gonna stand by

33:12.830 --> 33:15.000
and watch this woman
kill herself?

33:16.620 --> 33:19.750
All we said to each other
after Jon died

33:19.750 --> 33:22.170
was, uh,
"How could we not see it?"

33:22.170 --> 33:24.000
Right?
How could we not know?

33:24.000 --> 33:25.670
How could we not know?
Well, we know!

33:25.670 --> 33:28.960
She's standing right here
in front of us, and she is sick!

33:28.960 --> 33:30.380
And we know!!

33:32.580 --> 33:33.920
Shame on all of you!

33:35.710 --> 33:37.290
Shame on all of you.

33:38.960 --> 33:41.620
But you know what? It doesn't
matter anyway, does it, Maggie?

33:41.620 --> 33:42.960
No.

33:42.960 --> 33:44.960
'Cause you're gonna bail on them
just like you bailed

33:44.960 --> 33:46.380
on all your friends
in Chicago.

33:46.380 --> 33:47.580
Isn't that right?

33:47.580 --> 33:48.960
Where you off to next?

33:48.960 --> 33:51.000
I hear it's lovely in Baltimore
this time of year.

33:51.000 --> 33:52.210
Gary, stop.

33:52.210 --> 33:54.380
All because some loser
named Chad broke your heart?

33:54.380 --> 33:59.250
[ Voice breaking ] Don't ever
say that name again ever.

33:59.250 --> 34:01.380
You don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

34:01.380 --> 34:04.040
♪♪

34:04.040 --> 34:07.120
You're right. I don't know
what I'm talking about.

34:07.120 --> 34:08.120
[ Sniffles ]

34:08.120 --> 34:10.250
♪♪

34:10.250 --> 34:11.670
I don't know you.

34:11.670 --> 34:13.920
♪♪

34:13.920 --> 34:15.670
[ Sighs ]

34:15.670 --> 34:17.620
[ Door opens ]

34:17.620 --> 34:19.170
[ Door closes ]

34:24.290 --> 34:25.620
You okay?

34:25.620 --> 34:28.460
[ Sighs ]

34:28.460 --> 34:29.500
No.

34:31.210 --> 34:33.620
No, I'm the exact opposite
of okay.

34:35.210 --> 34:37.250
For the record,
I agree with you.

34:37.250 --> 34:38.250
[ Sighs ]

34:38.250 --> 34:39.500
After what happened
to Jon,

34:39.500 --> 34:41.290
we need to fight
for our friends.

34:41.290 --> 34:43.420
[ Sighs ]

34:43.420 --> 34:45.790
You look like
you could use a drink.

34:45.790 --> 34:50.500
No, I'm already sweating
and screaming at people.

34:50.500 --> 34:53.330
Probably not
a good idea.

34:53.330 --> 34:57.210
Not even one
for the birthday girl?

34:57.210 --> 35:00.080
Today's your birthday?

35:00.080 --> 35:02.620
Yeah, see, I didn't say anything
because I didn't want

35:02.620 --> 35:05.460
to take the spotlight away
from Regina and Delilah.

35:05.460 --> 35:07.080
I had a different plan.

35:09.460 --> 35:10.540
I know
you don't like birthdays.

35:10.540 --> 35:13.040
No, I don't like
my birthday.

35:13.040 --> 35:15.120
I'm -- [ Sighs ]

35:15.120 --> 35:17.420
I'm on fairly good terms
with other people's.

35:19.080 --> 35:21.210
So...

35:21.210 --> 35:24.120
You do want to go
have a drink?

35:24.120 --> 35:26.080
Sure, as long
as it's not wine.

35:28.170 --> 35:29.290
Thank you.

35:31.000 --> 35:33.540
So...

35:33.540 --> 35:35.620
So,
those are my friends.

35:35.620 --> 35:37.710
[ Chuckles ]

35:37.710 --> 35:39.460
I owe you an apology.

35:39.460 --> 35:41.920
Not at all.
They seem cool.

35:41.920 --> 35:44.500
They just happen to be dealing
with a lot right now.

35:44.500 --> 35:46.460
If I'm being honest...

35:46.460 --> 35:50.210
♪♪

35:50.210 --> 35:51.790
...I used you tonight.

35:51.790 --> 35:56.710
♪♪

35:56.710 --> 35:58.330
I felt rejected by Eddie,

35:58.330 --> 36:02.250
and a part of me liked

36:02.250 --> 36:05.250
having him see me
with someone else.

36:06.500 --> 36:10.540
A very smart,
good-looking someone else.

36:12.330 --> 36:14.080
Apology and compliment
accepted.

36:14.080 --> 36:15.790
[ Chuckles ]

36:15.790 --> 36:17.790
Hey, and trust me,

36:17.790 --> 36:21.000
I know that divorce
can be complicated.

36:21.000 --> 36:23.580
Wanting to make your ex jealous
doesn't make you a bad person.

36:23.580 --> 36:26.330
It just makes you
a human person.

36:26.330 --> 36:27.380
Thank you.

36:29.080 --> 36:31.620
And if we were
to ever go out,

36:31.620 --> 36:34.170
I'd want it to be
for the right reasons.

36:34.170 --> 36:35.750
And if we were
ever to go out,

36:35.750 --> 36:37.580
maybe we could
limit it to...

36:37.580 --> 36:40.710
three or four
of your friends, tops?
[ Laughs ]

36:40.710 --> 36:44.000
I can work with that.

36:44.000 --> 36:47.580
Well, tonight was,
uh...

36:47.580 --> 36:49.290
Yeah.

36:49.290 --> 36:53.210
♪♪

36:53.210 --> 36:56.330
All right, well,
thank you.

36:56.330 --> 36:58.540
♪ I don't know ♪

36:58.540 --> 36:59.830
Drive safe.

37:02.080 --> 37:05.620
♪ If she ran away,
if she ran away ♪

37:05.620 --> 37:06.790
Uh, one more thing.

37:06.790 --> 37:07.880
Hmm?

37:07.880 --> 37:10.420
♪♪

37:13.670 --> 37:19.040
♪♪

37:19.040 --> 37:24.380
♪♪

37:24.380 --> 37:26.880
♪ Just come home ♪

37:26.880 --> 37:36.540
♪♪

37:36.540 --> 37:37.830
[ Sighs ]

37:37.830 --> 37:43.710
♪♪

37:43.710 --> 37:47.500
♪♪

37:49.120 --> 37:51.040
Uh, he was my brother.

37:51.040 --> 37:53.880
And he was 19.

37:53.880 --> 37:56.960
And he had been drinking,

37:56.960 --> 38:00.500
which is something that he did
to self-medicate

38:00.500 --> 38:03.710
for his depression.

38:03.710 --> 38:06.210
[ Sighs ]

38:06.210 --> 38:10.040
And I had stopped him
so many times before.

38:10.040 --> 38:13.330
That night, my friends
wanted to go to the movies,

38:13.330 --> 38:17.380
and so I chose
to go with them.

38:17.380 --> 38:21.170
♪♪

38:21.170 --> 38:23.040
And...

38:23.040 --> 38:24.790
[ Sighs ]

38:24.790 --> 38:30.620
...I can't help but think
that if I hadn't gone,

38:30.620 --> 38:33.290
[ Voice breaking ]
Chad would still be here.

38:33.290 --> 38:34.290
I'm really sorry.

38:34.290 --> 38:36.210
You know, the paramedics said
that he, um,

38:36.210 --> 38:40.710
he died as soon
as he hit the tree, so...

38:40.710 --> 38:43.000
since then,
I've pretty much spent my life

38:43.000 --> 38:46.000
t-trying to keep people
from hitting the tree.

38:46.000 --> 38:47.380
You can't blame yourself.

38:47.380 --> 38:49.330
You can't say that.

38:49.330 --> 38:50.330
You don't know.

38:50.330 --> 38:52.540
I didn't stop him.

38:52.540 --> 38:53.580
[ Sniffles ]

38:53.580 --> 38:56.170
He needed me,
and I wasn't there.

38:57.790 --> 38:59.620
And now he's gone.

38:59.620 --> 39:02.880
♪♪

39:02.880 --> 39:06.290
Is that why
you won't save yourself?

39:06.290 --> 39:13.330
♪♪

39:13.330 --> 39:20.460
♪♪

39:20.460 --> 39:22.120
[ Laughs ]

39:22.120 --> 39:27.040
♪♪

39:27.040 --> 39:28.540
Oh...

39:28.540 --> 39:31.540
♪ However far away ♪

39:31.540 --> 39:34.880
♪♪

39:34.880 --> 39:39.670
♪ I will always love you ♪

39:41.330 --> 39:45.170
♪ However long I stay ♪

39:45.170 --> 39:47.380
♪♪

39:47.380 --> 39:50.500
Uh, see you Friday
at 1:00?

39:50.500 --> 39:51.620
Extra dressing.

39:51.620 --> 39:54.540
♪♪

39:54.540 --> 39:55.710
♪ I will always love you ♪

39:55.710 --> 39:57.540
Hey, Regina.

39:57.540 --> 40:00.580
I came back
because I wanted to thank you.

40:00.580 --> 40:04.420
♪♪

40:04.420 --> 40:07.000
It was great to be here

40:07.000 --> 40:09.330
and feel like
part of the gang again.

40:09.330 --> 40:11.330
Just so you know,
this evening

40:11.330 --> 40:14.420
was supposed to culminate
in a chocolate ganache cake.

40:14.420 --> 40:17.580
A much sweeter,
though less dramatic, finale

40:17.580 --> 40:19.330
than what was
on Gary's menu.

40:19.330 --> 40:20.830
[ Chuckles ]

40:20.830 --> 40:22.790
Want to try it,
tell me what you think?

40:22.790 --> 40:24.500
A sugary dessert?

40:24.500 --> 40:25.540
I love it.

40:25.540 --> 40:26.540
Mm-hmm.

40:26.540 --> 40:28.790
♪♪

40:28.790 --> 40:29.790
Mmm.

40:29.790 --> 40:30.960
Delilah gave it
a thumbs up,

40:30.960 --> 40:32.790
but, you know,
she's eating for two,

40:32.790 --> 40:34.330
so I wanted
a third opinion.

40:34.330 --> 40:35.420
What?

40:35.420 --> 40:36.420
Delilah's...

40:36.420 --> 40:37.960
Oh. I'm sorry.

40:37.960 --> 40:39.830
I thought you knew.

40:39.830 --> 40:41.290
No. Uh...

40:41.290 --> 40:42.290
It's Jon's.

40:42.290 --> 40:44.670
She's pregnant
with Jon's baby.

40:44.670 --> 40:47.000
[ Sighs ]

40:47.000 --> 40:48.080
Wow.

40:48.080 --> 40:50.380
And I thought
my life was complicated.

40:50.380 --> 40:54.120
♪ However far away ♪

40:54.120 --> 40:57.000
♪ I will always love you ♪

40:57.000 --> 41:00.670
♪ However long I stay ♪

41:00.670 --> 41:02.670
My roommate's not home.
It's okay.

41:02.670 --> 41:04.080
That's perfect.

41:04.080 --> 41:05.000
Perfect.

41:05.000 --> 41:07.500
♪ Whatever words I say ♪

41:07.500 --> 41:10.580
♪ I will always love you ♪

41:10.580 --> 41:13.380
♪ I will always ♪

41:15.790 --> 41:17.040
♪ Love you ♪

41:17.040 --> 41:19.330
[ Groans ]

41:19.330 --> 41:20.620
[ Sighs ]

41:20.620 --> 41:26.330
♪♪

41:26.330 --> 41:27.790
Something wrong?

41:27.790 --> 41:31.120
♪♪

41:31.120 --> 41:32.500
No.

41:32.500 --> 41:37.040
♪♪

41:37.040 --> 41:40.040
♪ Whenever I'm alone with you ♪

41:40.040 --> 41:43.670
[ Thunder crashing ]

41:43.670 --> 41:46.330
I'm sorry, Chad.
I can't -- I can't do it.

41:46.330 --> 41:47.330
Sure you can.

41:47.330 --> 41:50.120
No, it's no use!
We're going down!

41:50.120 --> 41:52.330
No, you're not, Mags.

41:52.330 --> 41:54.460
Pull up. Pull up.
There's one thing
you need to know.

41:56.000 --> 41:58.540
There's nothing
you could've done to save me.

41:58.540 --> 42:03.290
♪♪

42:03.290 --> 42:05.620
Oh, my God.

42:05.620 --> 42:08.000
[ Laughs ]
We're okay.

42:08.000 --> 42:09.670
We're okay.

42:09.670 --> 42:11.580
Where are you going?

42:11.580 --> 42:13.670
Hey, where are you going?

42:13.670 --> 42:16.830
This is where I leave you.

42:16.830 --> 42:20.170
♪ Whatever words I say ♪

42:20.170 --> 42:21.210
♪ I will always... ♪

42:25.580 --> 42:34.080
♪♪

42:34.080 --> 42:43.120
♪♪

42:43.120 --> 42:52.170
♪♪

42:52.170 --> 43:01.210
♪♪
